passages.text: This week, we had results out from Softcat (FY25) and SoftwareOne (2Q25), with the latter pointing to implied weaker forward guidance. We also share work from our global colleagues, including the initiation of Figma and on AI's ROI in the Back Office.

SoftwareOne: In- line 2Q25, but lowered guidance will weigh. Revenue down \(4.3\%\) y/y in cc, which is c. 1pp better than consensus, and adj. EBITDA of CHF 68.6m, in- line with consensus. Combined LfL FY25 guidance with Crayon indicates flat revenue and adj. EBITDA margin \(>20\%\) . Expectations for Crayon merger synergies unchanged.

Softcat: FY25 Trading Update - Upside to '25 growth, but '26 guidance may disappoint. Continued conversion of larger deals driving further upside to FY25 growth estimate. Company now expects mid teens growth in operating profit (2% above street). FY26 guide pointing to low double digit gross profit growth and high single digit operating profit growth excluding large deal impact, but the base effect (we think no large deals assumed in FY26) means reported gross profit / operating profit growth is expected to be high / low single digit. We estimate that this implies a c. 4% cut to consensus operating profit forecasts.

Figma: High- Quality Design Meets High- Quality Price; Initiating at Equal- weight. Figma's product design platform enables collaboration across the design process, widening its user base and driving durable growth. Strong record of innovation, clear market leadership and solid unit economics underpin a high- quality business, but at \(>35x\) sales, risk/reward looks balanced.

Is AI Driving the Biggest ROI in the Back Office? With AI having the biggest ROI in the back office, we expect AI budget dollars to increasingly flow there. Back office buyers are typically risk averse, so meaningful revenue contribution to software vendors likely takes time (2H26- 2027). WDAY, OS, & MANH are key back office vendors to watch.

Snowflake: 2Q26 Results: Riding the Data Transformation Wave. A strong core + traction in adj markets results in FY26 product revenue growth outlook rising to \(+27\%\) vs. \(+25\%\) prior. Remain OW as SNOW is best way to play the data modernization theme in Software.
